This paper is about multi-objective reinforcement learning (MORL) with linear preferences, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new algorithm for MORL that enables few-shot adaptation to new tasks. The paper also discusses the challenges of learning a single model to produce optimal policies under different preference conditions. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
